    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>*In nomine sancte et individue Trinitatis <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king #kinOf #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Imperial/royal_diploma"
                            ref="#people/127">Heinricus</persName> divina favente clementia quartus
                        Romanorum <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus.* Cum lubrici
                        saeculi condicio brevis sit et incerta, divinitus ammonemur ut in hac valle
                        lacrimarum dum tempus habemus seramus quod in futuro cum gaudio metamus.
                        Quapropter omnibus Christi nostrique fidelibus tam futuris quam presentibus
                        notum fieri volumus, qualiter nos rogatu et petitione fidelium principum
                        nostrorum, ob interventum etiam <rs key="#Abbots">abbatis</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Abbots" ref="#juridical_persons/2091">Cluniacensis</orgName>
                        <persName key="#Abbots #kinOf" ref="#people/3538">Pontii</persName> nostri dilecti <rs
                            key="#kinOf">consanguinei</rs>, et memoriam <rs key="#nephew/nieceOf"
                            >neptis</rs> nostrae <persName key="#Countess #nephew/nieceOf"
                            ref="#people/125">Mathildis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Countess">comitissae</rs>, <rs key="#Monasteries">abbaciam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Imperial/royal_diploma #Landed_possessions #Hay/fodder #Animals #Forests #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Ports #Mills #Roads#Agricultural_workers #Specialized_workers #Immunity"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2001">Sancti Benedicti in Arione</orgName> quam
                        antecessores ipsius ecclesiae Cluniacensi pro salute et remedio animarum
                        suarum subdiderunt <rs key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">sub mundiburdio
                            nostre tuitionis</rs> suscepimus, et quicquid Mathildis eidem aecclesie
                        donavit, dum vixit, et moriens dimisit, nos donamus et nostra imperiali
                        auctoritate confirmamus, cum omnibus appendiciis, <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">cultis et incultis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder"
                            >pratis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder #Animals">pasquis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">venationibus</rs>, vallis,
                        areis, aquis, <rs key="#Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">aquarumque
                            decursibus</rs>, <rs key="#Ports">molis</rs>, <rs key="#Mills"
                            >molendinis</rs>, <rs key="#Roads">viis et in viis exitibus</rs> et
                        reditibus et <rs key="#Agricultural_workers #Specialized_workers">familia
                            utriusque sexus</rs> et omni utilitate quae inde exire vel contingre
                        possunt. Precipimus etiam ut <rs key="#Immunity">nullus archiepiscopus,
                            episcopus, marchio, comes, vicecomes, scultatius, gastaldio, vicedominus
                            audeat predictam abbatiam de predictis bonis inquietare, molestare vel
                            disvestire</rs>. Si quis vero quod absit huius nostri <rs
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">precepti paginam</rs> temerario ausu
                        contraire temptaverit, <rs key="#Penalty">auri libras centum componat</rs>,
                        medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere nostre</rs> et medietatem
                        supradicto loco. Quod ut verius credatur et ab omnibus inviolabiliter
                        observetur hanc cartam inde conscriptam et manu propria corroboratam
                        impressione nostri sigilli insigniri iussimus. Signum Domini Heinrici Quarti
                        Imperatoris Invictissimi. <persName
                            key="#Chancellor #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/3513"
                            >Burchardus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> vice <persName
                            key="#Archbishops #Archchancellor" ref="#people/3537"
                            >Federici</persName>
                        <placeName key="#Archbishops" ref="#places/1850">Coloniensis</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs> recognivit. Data XIII Kal. Januarii. Indict.
                        VIII. Anno dominicae incarnatiorus millesimo C.XV. Regnante Heinrico Quarto
                        rege Romanorum anno XI, imperante V. Actum est <placeName ref="#places/2988"
                            >Spirae</placeName> in Christo feliciter. Amen. </ab>
